## `remove(conn, inode, name)`
<!-- checksum: xattrs-7 -->

### Failure Modes
- No row with `(inode, name)`: raises `NotFound`. **propagated**.

### Implementation Notes

```python
def remove(conn, inode, name):
    cur = conn.execute(
        "DELETE FROM xattrs WHERE inode = ? AND name = ?",
        (inode, name),
    )
    if cur.rowcount == 0:
        raise NotFound(f"xattr {name!r} not set on inode {inode}")
```

### Test Strategy
- `test_xattrs.test_removexattr_*`

